A cyclist was injured in a collision with a car while he was cycling on Murray Road in Pietermaritzburg on Sunday, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene and found both the man and his fianc on the side of the road. Upon assessment, paramedics found that the man had sustained several injuries, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. Paramedics treated the man and he was then transported to Northdale Hospital for further care. A car that had been involved in the collision was parked a short distance away. The driver fortunately escaped injury, he said.